node.text:
Four Roses’ 2021 Limited Edition Small Batch launches in September

“Latest release is highest proof in the Limited Edition series, featuring barrels aged 12 to 16 years.

Four Roses Distillery will issue the newest release in its series of limited-quantity special bottlings this September – the 2021 Limited Edition Small Batch.

Non-chill filtered and bottled at 114.2 proof, the 2021 Limited Edition Small Batch features four different hand-selected batches aged 12 to 16 years. These batches represent four of the distillery’s 10 distinct Bourbon recipes – a 16-year-old Bourbon from the OBSV recipe, a 14-year-old OBSQ, a 12-year-old OESK, and a 16-year-old OESV. “

- @fourrosesbourbon 

———————————————————————————

#bourbon #bourbonwhiskey #bourbonenthusiast #whiskey #whisky #cheers #drinks #slainte #imbibe #fourroses #fourroseslimitededition #🥃

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bourbon Enthusiast on August 29, 2021 tagging @bluenotebourbon. May be an image of bottle and text that says 'BLUE NOTE CROSSROADS CBOURB ENTHUSIAS STRAIGHT FINISHED WITH BOURBON WHISKEY TOASTED FRENCH DAK CRAFTED CRAFTEDMEMPHIS MEMPHIS 100 PROOF'.

node.text:
“Crossroads” is the latest release from Blue Note and it’s a rich, dessert-like pour with minimal spice. Finished with toasted French oak, it’s very smooth and dangerously easy to drink at 100 proof. Solid entry into the finished category @bluenotebourbon 🥃

———————————————————————————

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bourbon Enthusiast on August 28, 2021 tagging @highbankco_. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Batch 2 of Whiskey War Double Oaked: It has all the earthy and spice qualities of a rye, with layers of heavy oak and sweet barrel char thrown in. The additional 14 to 19 months of secondary aging really thickened up the body and taste profile over the original. 

———————————————————————————

node.text:
Releasing this September, Blue Run’s Golden Rye Whiskey is unique and tasty. The rye notes are subtle and give way to layers of caramel, honey and a touch of peppery spice on the finish. It has a nice, buttery texture and is somewhat sweeter than anticipated. Solid pour 👍

———————————————————————————

node.text:
At 11 years old, this release is dominated by dry oak notes followed by baking spice and honey. Of the brand’s most recent releases, the Old Fitzgerald Fall 2021 Edition isn’t the heaviest hitter but still a solid well-aged wheater.
